Ingredients.10: 2 (16 ounce) packages imitation chicken breast halves (seitan), cut into 1-inch wide strips

Directions.1: Pour flour onto a large plate. Place eggs in a shallow bowl. Combine bread crumbs, garlic powder, paprika, cayenne pepper, black pepper, chili powder, and salt in another shallow bowl.

Directions.2: Coat imitation chicken strips in flour, dip into eggs, then dredge in bread crumb mixture, and place on a plate.

Directions.3: Heat an air fryer to 500 degrees F (260 degrees C).

Directions.4: Place a row of coated strips in the air fryer basket. Spray with a light coat of cooking spray.

Directions.5: Cook strips in the air fryer for 6 minutes. Open fryer to flip strips with tongs. Continue cooking until golden brown, 4 to 6 minutes more.
